# Conventional Commits

Follow [Conventional Commits 1.0.0](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/) for every commit in this repository.

## Format

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- Use lowercase type.
- Description: imperative mood, no trailing period, ~72 chars max.
- Body and footers are optional; separate them from the title with a blank line.

## Types

| Type | Use when |
|------|----------|
| `feat` | New feature (MINOR in SemVer) |
| `fix` | Bug fix (PATCH in SemVer) |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `style` | Formatting, no logic change |
| `refactor` | Code change, not feat/fix |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `test` | Tests only |
| `build` | Build system or dependencies |
| `ci` | CI configuration |
| `chore` | Maintenance (e.g. `.gitignore`) |
| `revert` | Revert a prior commit |

Breaking changes: append `!` after type/scope (`feat!:`) or add footer `BREAKING CHANGE: <description>`.

## Examples

```
feat(profile): add interactive timeline section
fix(nav): correct mobile menu z-index
docs: update README setup steps
chore: exclude docs directory from version control
```

## When committing

- One logical change per commit when possible.
- Match the repo's existing scope names if scopes are already in use.
- The `.githooks/commit-msg` hook validates format locally when hooks are enabled.
